Poland plans to extend a ban on international flights by two weeks until June 6 due to the coronavirus pandemic, state-run news agency PAP said on Friday citing infrastructure ministry documents. A ban on domestic flights will be extended by eight days until May 31, PAP also said. Poland’s state-owned airline PLL LOT said earlier in May that it would not resume flights before the end of May. As of Thursday, Poland has reported 19,983 coronavirus cases, including 965 deaths. (Reuters) YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Buy and read digital replicas of your TRIBUNE titles by subscribing through E-VENDING WHO Considers Madagascar’s COVID Organics For Clinical Observation
